org.spongepowered.api.world.gen.populator

Interface EndIsland

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Populator

    public interface EndIsland
extends Populator
    Represents a populator which will generate small 'islands' which float in the end.

    The island is formed as a cone with each layer being a circle of blocks with a gradually decreasing radius.

      • getExclusionRadius

        int getExclusionRadius()
        Gets the radius around the center (0, 0) of the world that this populator will not apply to.

        This is used to prevent the islands from generating around the ender dragon fight area.

        Returns:
        The radius
